main event: On November 7, 1957, in Fort Deposit, Alabama, a civilian witnessed a white opaque circular object traveling in a circular glide to the left at an estimated altitude of 200 ft.
interesting points: The object was described as white opaque and circular, exhibiting unusual movement patterns.
The document indicates that there was insufficient data for proper evaluation of the sighting.
The sketch included in the document depicts the object moving rapidly in concentric circles to the left at 200 feet altitude.
The report makes reference to Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program to investigate unidentified flying objects (UFOs).
Handwritten notes and comments on the document suggest a lack of conclusive analysis or information about the observed object.
